    schema:identifier "Slide1" ;
    fxs:extractedTextCorpus "Exit; If additional reference materials are included with this course, they can be accessed from the Resource menu at the top right of the course window.\\n \\nNotes: \\nMany reference materials are provided as Adobe PDF files. To read these documents, you must have the free Adobe Acrobat Reader installed. Go to https://get.adobe.com/reader to install Acrobat Reader if needed.\\r \\nLinks may lead to external resources. Some of these may require membership in a specific organization. If you are interested in those resources, see that organization’s web site for more information.; You can exit the course at any time by selecting the Exit button in the top right. If you return to the course at a later date, you can pick-up right where you left off. \\n\\nWhen you reach the end of the course, you will also be able to Exit using a button on the last page.; A playbar is provided at the bottom of the course. Buttons on the playbar allow you to pause, play, rewind, and fast forward through audio and" .

<https://interego-css.livelysky-8b81abb0.eastus.azurecontainerapps.io/markj/courses/lesson3/slide/6IcYxMXh0mW> a fxs:Slide ;
    dcterms:title "About This Course" ;
    fxs:identifiedBy "6IcYxMXh0mW" ;
    fxs:sequenceIndex 1 ;
    fxs:fileLocator "package!/html5/data/js/6IcYxMXh0mW.js" ;
    prov:wasDerivedFrom <https://interego-css.livelysky-8b81abb0.eastus.azurecontainerapps.io/markj/courses/lesson3/res/__69JeglEuzyv_RES> ;
    schema:identifier "Slide2" ;
    fxs:extractedTextCorpus "template3.jpg; About EPRI\\n\\nFounded in 1972, EPRI is the world’s preeminent independent, non-profit energy research and development organization, with offices around the world. EPRI’s trusted experts collaborate with more than 450 companies in 45 countries, driving innovation to ensure the public has clean, safe, reliable, affordable, and equitable access to electricity across the globe. Together, we are shaping the future of energy.\\n\\n; Disclaimer; Select each item on the right to learn more about this course and EPRI.; This course does not contain audio. ; Inverter-Based Resource (IBR) Basics and Operations\\n\\nEPRI Product ID # 3002033926\\r\\nCopyright © 2025 Electric Power Research Institute, Inc. All rights reserved. \\r\\nEPRI reserves all rights in the Program as delivered. The Program or any portion thereof may not be reproduced in any form whatsoever except as provided by license without the written consent of EPRI. A license under EPRI's rights in the Program may be available d" .

